text: hey guys, just an update on my little slack summarizer experiment - i've been using paperbot and slack-digest for a few days now, and so far I find slack-digest to be pretty useful.  Paperbot just gives you links, but slack-digest gives you tidy summaries of any channel you subscribe to.  it's a decent way to catch up on conversations.  To use it, DM slack-digest and type "subscribe #channel-name", and the digest bot will DM you a summary for that channel if it's active in the AM.
I'd be curious to find out what you guys think of it, so give it a try if you want
